<p>

A <b>resource</b>, or <b>system resource</b>, is any physical or virtual component of limited availability within a computer system. Every device connected to a computer system is a resource. Every internal system component is a resource. Virtual system resources include <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../077/7077.xml">
files</link>, network connections and memory areas.</p>

